---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';

const title = "Get 3D Scan of Yourself at Home | Free 3D Software for Kinect";
const description = "3D printed figurines: 3D print yourself using a 3D portrait made in Shapify Booth.";
---

<Layout {title} {description}>
</div>
<div class='page-kinect'>
<h1>
At home
</h1>
<div class='carousel-bootstrap carousel slide carousel-photo-home' data-ride='carousel' id='carousel-photo-home'>
<div class='text-block-on-img'>
<div class='h1'>Make your own SHAPIE® at home, easy as 1-2-3!</div>
<p>
Now you can easily create a lifelike 3D model of yourself in the comfort of your own home!
Use a Kinect sensor to 3D scan yourself and use your 3D model for a wide variety of applications -
upload it to Sketchfab, share to Facebook, use it in a VR game or even print it out in 3D!
</p>
<a class="dotted" href="#tutorial">See our tutorial</a>
<a class="dotted" href="#download">Free software download</a>
<a href="/faq">FAQ</a>
</div>
<ol class='carousel-indicators clearfix'>
<li class='active cur-active' data-slide-to='0' data-target='#carousel-photo-home'></li>
<li data-slide-to='1' data-target='#carousel-photo-home'></li>
<li data-slide-to='2' data-target='#carousel-photo-home'></li>
<li data-slide-to='3' data-target='#carousel-photo-home'></li>
<li data-slide-to='4' data-target='#carousel-photo-home'></li>
</ol>
<div class='carousel-inner'>
<div class='item active'>
<img alt="3D scan yourself with friends" src="/assets/main_img/home_1-8de67e3280fb610fdd56fd8e2cba0b258e3282158915bddc3a7d94312e58fb18.jpg" />
</div>
<div class='item'>
<img alt="3D print mini-you" src="/assets/main_img/home_2-2b035202b2b8368097322cc69f68b9e3aadd889e426ee68bd8bce9acd4ab25d6.jpg" />
</div>
<div class='item'>
<img alt="Scan yourself in seated position" src="/assets/main_img/home_3-f6a6dc2c20328d5125db6383801cbf72e8ac554ea9580d9ba6130ad8e99e3fc9.jpg" />
</div>
<div class='item'>
<img alt="3D scan yourself for fun" src="/assets/main_img/home_4-b4fd4097dbed684fcdb0fd7a8eeb57caeed9dd74e2e09b28562cd324150b309b.jpg" />
</div>
<div class='item'>
<img alt="Scan yourself for scale model" src="/assets/main_img/home_5-79463091bdf6d02ecc82e97694f0c17e6a68c37a66f9f94e4293f3e484766d13.jpg" />
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class='text-width'>
<div class='kinect-block row'>
<div class='col-md-6 p1'>
<h3>How to do it</h3>
<div class='img'></div>
<p>
Using the Shapify.me software, you can create your own 3D selfies from home.
All you need is a Kinect and the software, which you can download for free.
To start scanning, just follow a few simple steps, prompted by the software. Upload the 3D model to
<a href="https://sketchfab.com/">Sketchfab</a>, use it for VR or print it out in 3D.
</p>
</div>
<div class='col-md-6 p2'>
<h3>Don't have a Kinect?</h3>
<div class='img'></div>
<p>
<span class='text-purple'>A:</span>
Either find our
<a href="/scanning-point">nearest scanning point</a>
</p>
<p>
<span class='text-purple'>B:</span>
Or buy a Microsoft Kinect from <a target="_blank" href="http://www.ebay.com">Ebay</a>,
<a target="_blank" href="http://www.amazon.com">Amazon</a>, or other stockists.
</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<h3>
<a class='anchor' name='tutorial'>Tutorial</a>
</h3>
<p class='text-grey text-center'>Are you ready for scanning?</p>
<div class='carousel-tutorial-home carousel slide clearfix' data-ride='carousel' id='carousel-tutorial-home'>
<a role="button" data-slide="prev" class="left carousel-control pull-left" href="#carousel-tutorial-home"><span class='glyphicon glyphicon-chevron-left'></span>
</a><ol class='carousel-indicators clearfix pull-left row'>
<li class='col-md-4 active cur-active' data-slide-to='0' data-target='#carousel-tutorial-home'>Set up</li>
<li class='col-md-4' data-slide-to='1' data-target='#carousel-tutorial-home'>Scan</li>
<li class='col-md-4 pull-right' data-slide-to='2' data-target='#carousel-tutorial-home'>Upload</li>
</ol>
<a role="button" data-slide="next" class="right carousel-control pull-left" href="#carousel-tutorial-home"><span class='glyphicon glyphicon-chevron-right'></span>
</a><div class='clearfix'></div>
<div class='carousel-inner'>
<div class='item active row'>
<div class='col-md-4 first'>
<div class='top-block p1'>
<div class='img'></div>
</div>
<div class='bottom-block'>
<div class='title'>The Kinect sensor</div>
Place your Kinect roughly at the level of your chest and
make sure that no objects are obstructing the sensor.
You may want to use a tripod to hold the Kinect.
</div>
</div>
<div class='col-md-4'>
<div class='top-block p2'>
<div class='img'></div>
</div>
<div class='bottom-block'>
<div class='title'>The scanning space</div>
The scanning area should be an empty area of roughly 2x2 sq.m., where you can easily make 45 degree turns.
Make sure to remove unwanted objects in that area such as chairs, floor lamps, or cats.
</div>
</div>
<div class='col-md-4 last'>
<div class='top-block p3'>
<div class='img'></div>
</div>
<div class='bottom-block'>
<div class='title'>Good lighting</div>
Check how well the room will be lit during scanning.
The subject should be lit as uniformly as possible.
Avoid backlights to the sensor and strong specular reflections or shadows on the subject.
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class='item row'>
<div class='col-md-4 first'>
<div class='top-block p4'>
<div class='img'></div>
</div>
<div class='bottom-block'>
Install the Shapify.me software on your computer.
Connect the Kinect sensor to your computer and plug the power cable into a socket.
Run the application. Press "Capture" to start scanning.
</div>
</div>
<div class='col-md-4'>
<div class='top-block p5'>
<div class='img'></div>
</div>
<div class='bottom-block'>
Stand about 1m away from the Kinect and strike a pose you can repeat each time you turn around.
Follow the voice instructions. For each turn, remember to keep the same facial expression and pose.
</div>
</div>
<div class='col-md-4 last'>
<div class='top-block p6'>
<div class='img'></div>
</div>
<div class='bottom-block'>
Once the scanning is done, your captured data will take a few minutes to process.
Then voila, your 3D scan is ready! Check your digital model by spinning it around.
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class='item row'>
<div class='col-md-6 first'>
<div class='top-block p7'>
<div class='img'></div>
</div>
<div class='bottom-block'>
<div class='title'>Your final 3D model</div>
Once the scanning is done, your captured data will take a few minutes to process.
Then voila, your 3D scan is ready! Check your digital model by spinning it around.
</div>
</div>
<div class='col-md-6 last'>
<div class='top-block p8'>
<div class='img'></div>
</div>
<div class='bottom-block'>
<div class='title'>Next steps</div>
Your 3D model will be uploaded to the online gallery on www.shapify.me.
You can also purchase your 3D model and upload it to Sketchfab,
and use it to customise your gaming or other VR experience or simply get it
printed out in 3D to make for a fantastic gift.
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class='text-width'>
If you'd like more help on scanning yourself, please download the
<a stream="true" target="_blank" download="Shapify_User_Guide.pdf" href="http://docs.artec-group.com/shapify/home.pdf">user guide</a>.
</div>
<div class='row download-block'>
<div class='col-md-4 os'>
<div class='os-block'>
<div class='win-os dotted link active'>Windows</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class='col-md-4 system'>
<a class='anchor h3' name='download'>System Requirements</a>
<ul>
<li>Microsoft Kinect for Windows V1</li>
<li>Intel Core i5 processor (2011 year or later)</li>
<li>8 GB RAM minimum</li>
<li>64-bit processor</li>
<li>Audio Speakers</li>
<li>
Kinect for Windows should use
<br>
either USB 2.0 or USB 3.0
</li>
<li>Internet Connection</li>
<li class='soft-block download_pc active'>Windows 7(x64) or later</li>
<li class='soft-block download_mac'>OS X 10.9 - 10.11. MacOS is not supported</li>
</ul>
</div>
<div class='col-md-4'>
<div class='h3'>Download Software</div>
<div class='soft-block download_pc active'>
<ul class='info'>
<li>Updated: June  3, 2014</li>
<li>Version: 1.2.0.1</li>
<li>Language: English</li>
</ul>
<div class='action-download'><a onClick="gaqPushTrackEvent(&#39;win&#39;, &#39;Download&#39;, &#39;1.2.0.1&#39;);" href="softwares/win/1-2-0-1-win/download%3Faction_type=download"><span class="btn btn-warning">Download</span></a></div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class='text-width'>
Did you know that we can also create an <a target="_blank" href="https://www.iphone3dscanner.com">app for the new iPhone X&#39;s 3D scanner</a> upon request?
</div>
</div>

</div>
<div class='footer-booth-wrapper'>
<div class='footer-bottom-booth'>
</Layout>